alysis for the Lakers vs. Rockets WCSF series! I have Lakers in 6!

These two teams are built entirely differently. The Lakers dominate in the paint, averaging the highest FG% at the rim in the NBA. They have two of the top 5 players in the NBA in LeBron & AD who like to work down low. They also are really strong defensively. They‚Äôre great defending the half court, they guard the 3 and the rim well, and they force turnovers. Houston‚Äôs offense is all about Harden and Russ in isolation driving for layups or kicking out to 3 point shooters. They are great at getting to the line and are also a solid defensive team. Houston‚Äôs biggest weakness is their interior defense, which bodes well for the Lakers. However, when the Rockets get hot from 3, the Lakers will struggle to keep up. When Houston goes cold, they start beating themselves and their entire offensive identity crumbles apart. I trust the Lakers offense pounding the ball inside more than Houston‚Äôs live and die by the 3 offense. The Lakers guard play which has struggled at times is a key to watch for, while for Houston they need their shooters to be locked in to have a chance at the upset.

